Key Arguments: The legislation infringes on the constitutional right to freedom of speech.
Free speech is essential for a thriving democracy and allows individuals to express their opinions and gather information.
The bill would lead to censorship and oppression of Australians' rights to form their own opinions.
Individuals should have the autonomy to determine what is right or wrong without external interference.
Notable Quotes: It is our fundamental right and the importance of a democratic society to have free speech, free opinion and free discourse.
This bill should NOT get passed as it will censor and oppress free Australians right to their own opinion.
